Class NodeStyleImpl<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ginsim.core.graph.view.style.BaseStyle<NodeStyle<V>>
      • org.ginsim.core.graph.view.style.NodeStyleImpl<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - vertex v
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeStyle<V>, Style
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultDynamicNodeStyle, DefaultHTGNodeStyle, DefaultRegulatoryNodeStyle, DefaultTreeNodeStyle
    public class NodeStyleImpl<V>
extends BaseStyle<NodeStyle<V>>
implements NodeStyle<V>
    Simple implementation for NodeStyle. It can be used to override a parent style (defining some properties) or as default style (defining all properties).
    Author:
    Aurelien Naldi

        public StyleProperty[] getProperties()
        Description copied from interface: Style
        Retrieve all properties used by this style. The default set of properties matches visual properties, but each style can use a different set of properties. For example, the default style for edges in a regulatory graph has several properties for edge colors: positive, negative, dual.
        Specified by:
        getProperties in interface Style
        Returns:
